title: Luke LeBlanc – studio session at The Current (music + interview)
description:
Minnesota-based singer-songwriter Luke LeBlanc recently released his fourth full album. Entitled “Fugue State,” the album was produced by musician and producer Erik Koskinen at Koskinen’s home studio in Cleveland, Minnesota.

Luke LeBlanc and his band recently visited the Radio Heartland studio for a session hosted by Mike Pengra. Watch the full session above.

Video segments
00:00:00 Take Your Mind Off It
00:03:22 Interview with host Mike Pengra, part 1
00:12:26 Come Clean
00:17:11 Interview with host Mike Pengra, part 2
00:24:55 Down Low

Band members
Luke LeBlanc - vocals, guitar
Erin Bekker - drums
Caz Falen - bass, backing vocals
Erik Koskinen - electric guitar
Ben Lester - pedal steel

Credits
Guest - Luke LeBlanc
Host - Mike Pengra
Producer - Mike Pengra

Audio - Evan Clark, Thor Cramer Bornemann

title: Neal Francis – Can't Stop The Rain (live for The Current)
description:
Chicago musician Neal Francis visited The Current studio while on tour in support of his album "In Plain Sight." During the session, he and his band performed the song "Can't Stop the Rain." Watch the full performance above.  

Band members
Neal Francis – vocals, piano
Kellen Boersma – guitar
Mike Starr – bass
Collin O’Brien – drums
